    "text": "article_7a88eb32-6db1-4110-9dcf-e6793bc20454 agent agent high 2026-07-05T04:13:53.999Z 2026-07-05T04:13:53.999Z article Getting started getting-started How to run Prism locally, where desktop distribution is headed, and what privacy defaults to expect. ## Recommended Local Run\n\nFor a full local stack, copy `.env.example` to `.env`, set the required secrets, and run Docker Compose. The web app opens at `http://localhost:18788`; API health is at `http://localhost:18787/health`.\n\n## Local Development\n\nFor source development, install the shared packages, config package, API, and web dependencies, pull the default Ollama models, then run `npm run dev` from the repo root. The root README lists the exact commands.\n\n## Private By Default\n\nPrism binds to loopback by default, so other devices on the network cannot connect unless network sharing is explicitly enabled. LOCAL mode should keep chat, auxiliary work, embeddings, and online-only image generation within the local privacy boundary.\n\n## Desktop Distribution\n\nOfficial desktop builds are free. GitHub Releases are the baseline delivery path for macOS, Windows, and Linux artifacts, with optional Patreon support treated as patronage rather than product access.\n\n## Launch Caveat\n\nThe product-worthy launch checklist is still pending. Broad public promotion should wait until platform artifacts, first-run setup, LOCAL privacy, support copy, and outreach materials have recorded pass evidence. Guides Quick start Install Prism concept_98e450e7-a536-4429-9c00-75d47211ac3e concept_d8ee0648-129b-427a-b6a7-dea62bb82e3e decision_791a7b3c-d069-4543-907d-3c0cda50f452 note_65e62737-730b-45ab-b59e-309f9888db4f README.md docs/distribution-model.md docs/product-worthy-launch.md audience:all getting-started distribution privacy"
